<topic id="dcpp_how_to_reset_the_page_numbers_after_the_toc">
  <title>How to Reset the Page Numbers after the TOC</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm product="author developer editor authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
            ><ph keyref="wysywig-or-html5-transformation"/><indexterm>Numbering<indexterm>Reset page
                numbers<indexterm>after
          table-of-contents</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm product="pdf-css">Numbering<indexterm>Reset page numbers<indexterm>after
              table-of-contents</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>In your <xref href="dcpp_the_customization_css.dita">customization CSS</xref>, use the
      following rule:</p>
    <codeblock outputclass="language-css">*[class ~= "map/map"] > *[class ~= "toc/toc"] + *[class ~= "topic/topic"]{
    counter-reset: page 1;
}</codeblock>
    <p>The effect is that it will reset the page number at the beginning of the first topic
      following the TOC.</p>
  </body>
